---
description: guides to chanseing the code.
globs:
alwaysApply: true
---

whenever you have to change anything in the code you must commit it right after.
every commit must have a self explanatory clear message.

if you have a group of related changes - create a new branch, do whatever you need, make sure it works (depending on the chnges not alway is a full test required but you alway must make sure that there are no critical errors related to the new chnges), than finaly merge back to the previous branch with a PR (create a PR review it yourself and approve \ disprove it).

all branch names should have a prefix like 'fix/' 'feature/' etc...


finally if any of the changes you made affect any of the running services \ containers you must remove those containers rebuild them and redeploy them to make sure they are up-to-date with the new code.




NOTE: this is super important unless spesificly asked not to, you should always finish in the same branch you started in.